  serving size: 292
servings: 2
---

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @linguine{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil.
Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

While the pasta cooks, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the pan is hot, add the @chorizo{60%g}(diced) and fry until it starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Next, add the garlic, stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir the @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @creme fraiche{150%g} and @water{75%ml} for the sauce into the pan.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, once the pasta is cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @peas{120%g} and the @hard Italian style cheese{20%g}(grated). Cook until the peas are piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the cooked pasta then taste and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if needed.

Add a splash of water if you feel it's needed.

Share the creamy chorizo linguine between your bowls.

Top with a handful of @wild rocket{20%g} and drizzle over the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} to finish.

Enjoy!